Tier 4 Province Crawlers - Implementation Log
===============================================
Updated: 2026-03-18

== BEIJING (crawlers/beijing.py, site_key: bj) ==

Status: COMPLETE - 1,781 docs, 1,761 with body (98.9%) in documents_new.db
Next step: merge into documents.db via scripts/merge_db.py

Sections and counts (list-only verified):
  szfwj  (市政府文件):         320 docs  - client-side pagination, .default_news li
  bgtwj  (市政府办公厅文件):    303 docs  - client-side pagination, .default_news li
  gfxwj  (规范性文件):          998 docs  - client-side pagination, .default_news li
  szfgz  (市政府规章):          135 docs  - server-side pagination (9 pages), card layout
  zcjd   (政策解读):             25 docs  - server-side pagination, standard list

Key discoveries:
  1. Beijing uses THREE different HTML templates across sections:
     - .default_news li with <b class="u_time"> for dates (szfwj, bgtwj)
     - .default_news li with <span> for dates (gfxwj)
     - p.c-bt-t / p.c-bt-c card layout for regulations (szfgz)
  2. Client-side pagination: JS does `var $list = $('.default_news li')` then
     `data.slice()` to paginate. ALL data is in the HTML. No API needed.
  3. createPageHTML(191, 13, 0, "index", "html") uses (records, pages, current)
     format - arg 2 is page count, NOT arg 1.
  4. SEO dummy entry with empty <i class="flag"></i> must be filtered out.
     Real entries have <i class="flag">是</i>.

Bugs fixed:
  - createPageHTML arg parsing: captured totalRecords (191) instead of totalPages (13)
  - WebFetch AI said <div class="c-bt-t"> but actual HTML uses <p class="c-bt-t">
  - Catastrophic regex backtracking on 1000-item page: extracted .default_news
    container first to reduce search space before running DOTALL patterns
  - SEO dummy entry filtered by checking flag content

Full crawl kicked off at 2026-03-17 with body fetching.

== JIANGSU (crawlers/jiangsu.py, site_key: js) ==

Status: PARTIAL - 1,041 docs listed, 0 with body (body extraction needs debugging)
DB: documents_new.db
Note: Body-fetch crawl ran but extracted 0 bodies. Likely needs _extract_body
  selector fixes for Jiangsu's HTML template. Only zcwj section (1/4) parses listings.

Sections (column IDs for jpage API):
  zcwj   (最新文件):     col84242  (~5184 docs per totalRecord)
  zcjd   (政策解读):     col84725
  xxgk   (政府信息公开): col84239
  szfgb  (省政府公报):   col81677

Architecture:
  - Uses jpage jQuery plugin with /module/web/jpage/dataproxy.jsp
  - First page: /col/col{id}/index.html (server-rendered)
  - Subsequent pages: dataproxy.jsp?startrecord=N&endrecord=M&columnid=ID
  - Doc URLs: /art/YYYY/M/D/art_{cat_id}_{art_id}.html

Fixed bugs:
  - jpage dataproxy.jsp returns XML with CDATA-wrapped HTML fragments.
    Added _extract_jpage_records() to extract CDATA content before parsing.
  - Dates in jpage responses have whitespace/newlines splitting them:
    "2026-\n01-\n23". Fixed regex to capture year/month/day separately
    with \s* between components.
  - Removed </li> requirement from end of pattern (a <span class="jds">
    block sits between the date span and </li>).
  - zcwj section: 3,049 docs from 50 pages (totalRecord was 5184 but
    we get ~60 items per jpage response, not the configured 20)

== SHANGHAI (crawlers/shanghai.py, site_key: sh) ==

Status: COMPLETE - 3,830 docs, 3,826 with body (99.9%) in documents_new.db
Base URL: https://www.shanghai.gov.cn

Sections (6 total, all working):
  nw39220  (沪府文件):    368 docs (14 year archives, 2013-2026)
  nw2407   (沪府令):      501 docs (24 year archives, 2003-2025)
  nw11407  (沪府发):    1,136 docs (23 year archives, 2003-2025)
  nw11408  (沪府办发):  1,039 docs (24 year archives, 2003-2026; 2025 broken on site)
  nw39221  (沪府办):      592 docs (14 year archives, 2013-2026)
  nw42944  (沪府规):      194 docs (9 year archives, 2018-2026)

Architecture:
  - Section index: /{section_id}/index.html
  - Year archives: scraped dynamically (inconsistent URL prefixes across years)
  - Pagination: jQuery plugin, totalPage:N, index.html / index_N.html
  - Doc URLs: /nw12344/YYYYMMDD/{uuid}.html
  - Body: div.Article_content
  - Dates in <span class="time">YYYY-MM-DD</span> (not plain text)
  - HTML comments contain duplicate entries — stripped before parsing

Fixed bugs:
  - Year-archive links have nested tags (<a><h4>2024年</h4></a>),
    not direct text. Fixed regex to use .*? with DOTALL.
  - Dates are in <span class="time">, not plain text after </a>.
    Research agent reported wrong structure.
  - Commented-out duplicates (<!-- ... -->) caused double-counting.
    Added comment stripping before parsing.

